|BKB*****        |CKBDarkWind's Rules on Multicharacters|BKB        *****|XX0
|BKB*************************************************************|XX0

|GKB1)|XX0 The only acceptable form of multicharacters are ones
   created by the game. If you create a second/third/etc
   character on your own, you are in violation of the rules,
   and all characters are subject to banishment. You can only
   create those characters in Darkwind, in the Multiple 
   Character Registration Room.
|GKB2)|XX0 If you are repeatedly found to create illegal characters,
   your site will be banned from the game.
|GKB3)|XX0 If you create and register multiple characters, all
   punishments and warnings apply to all.
|GKB4)|XX0 If any character is banished, you can not create a new
   character to take its place above the max character limit.
|GKB5)|XX0 You may only have ONE of your characters logged in at a
   time.
|GKB6)|XX0 In addition to your main character, you may register
   additional characters that are either normal or mythic. 
|GKB7)|XX0 You may only register a normal multi once your main
   character reaches CHAMPION (50). A second free slot is
   granted at LEGEND (150).
|GKB8)|XX0 You may register a mythic multi once your main
   character reaches LEGEND (150), both your main and second multi
   reach HERO (100), or you purchase an additional multichar slot
   with gold from the bank (10M per slot you already hold).
|GKB9)|XX0 You will login to your multi through your main account.
   This means that you will only need to remember one
   username/password combination, so please ensure you keep
   this login secure.
|GKB10)|XX0 You can purchase additional multichar slots up to
   10 total. Each slot will cost additional gold (10 million
   increase per).
|GKB11)|XX0 You can get a quick overview of your multichars
   with the |YKBmultirep|XX0 command.
|GKB12)|XX0 You can copy your main characters alias list
   with the |YKBmulticopy|XX0 command.
|GKB13)|XX0 All of your multis can access funds from your
   bank accounts with the |YKBtransfer|XX0 function built in
   at the bank. 

|GKB14)|XX0 All of your multis can access items from your
   storage room at the bank with the |YKBstore, retrieve,
   list|XX0 functions in the storage room.
